{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VJidhsRNL52iXqJSir4L2p","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Implementation History ŌĆö 306-fee-accounting-audit\n2\t\n3\tIteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\n4\tattempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\n5\tof every iteration to understand prior context.\n6\t\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\t## Iteration 1 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n10\t\n11\t**Item**: Create `backend/migrations/026_fee_accounting_audit.sql`.\n12\t\n13\t**Outcome**: Success.\n14\t\n15\t**Changes**:\n16\t- Added `backend/migrations/026_fee_accounting_audit.sql` with three tables:\n17\t  - `fee_allocation_events` ŌĆö allocation ledger. UNIQUE on `(source_type, source_id, wallet)`, CHECK that the three component lamport columns sum to `fee_lamports`, CHECK `referral_rate_bps BETWEEN 0 AND 10000`, plus a non-negative-amount guard. Indexed on `created_at`, with partial indexes on `referrer_user_id` and `user_id` (the audit snapshot's per-user/per-referrer queries).\n18\t  - `fee_bucket_debits` ŌĆö bucket debit ledger. UNIQUE on `(bucket, debit_type, source_id)`, CHECK `bucket IN ('referral','promotions','profit')`, CHECK status enum matches the spec. Indexed on `(bucket, status)` and `(created_at)`. Partial index on `(user_id, bucket, status)` for `getUserReferralAvailable`.\n19\t  - `fee_audit_checkpoints` ŌĆö bounded acceleration snapshots. Stores period bounds, row counts, bucket totals, ending balances, hashes. UNIQUE on `period_end`, plus a `period_end > period_start` guard.\n20\t\n21\t**Verification**:\n22\t- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (one pre-existing warning in `contracts/api-envelope.ts`, unchanged).\n23\t- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n24\t- Skipped vitest: this iteration is SQL only, no TS code changed.\n25\t\n26\t**Notes**:\n27\t- Added a `wallet` column to `fee_bucket_debits` to allow per-user queries to be human-debuggable; not strictly required by the spec but cheap.\n28\t- Added an `updated_at` column on debits ŌĆö needed for the lockstep claim/debit status sync in a later iteration.\n29\t- No data migration: ledger is go-forward only per FR-1 last bullet.\n30\t\n31\t## Iteration 1 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:36:11Z ŌĆö OK\n32\t- **Log**: iteration-001.log\n33\t\n34\t---\n35\t\n36\t## Iteration 2 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n37\t\n38\t**Item**: Create `backend/src/db/fee-accounting.ts` with `calculateFeeAllocation` helper and typed DB methods. Wire onto the `Db` interface.\n39\t\n40\t**Outcome**: Success.\n41\t\n42\t**Changes**:\n43\t- Added `backend/src/db/fee-accounting.ts`:\n44\t  - `calculateFeeAllocation(feeLamports, referrerRateBps)` ŌĆö pure FR-2 split (referral floor ŌåÆ promotions floor on remainder ├Ś 20% ŌåÆ profit absorbs dust). Validates non-negative integer fee + bps in `[0, 10000]`.\n45\t  - `insertFeeAllocation` ŌĆö writes one allocation row, idempotent on `(source_type, source_id, wallet)` via `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` + re-select.\n46\t  - `insertFeeBucketDebit` ŌĆö writes one debit row, idempotent on `(bucket, debit_type, source_id)`.\n47\t  - `updateFeeBucketDebitStatus(bucket, debitType, sourceId, status)` ŌĆö transitions debit status, bumps `updated_at`. Returns `undefined` if the row is missing.\n48\t  - `getReferralBucketAvailable()` ŌĆö global referral bucket: sum of allocation referral_lamports minus sum of `pending|processing|error|completed` referral debits.\n49\t  - `getUserReferralAvailable(userId)` ŌĆö per-user referrer balance, same shape.\n50\t  - `getFeeAuditSnapshot()` ŌĆö totals + per-bucket allocated/active/completed/pendingClaimReserves/failed/available, plus `invariantViolations` (rows where components ŌēĀ fee) and `overdrawnBuckets`. Treats `pending|processing|error|completed` as reserved/spent, excludes `failed`. `auditFrom` is `MIN(created_at)`.\n51\t- Wired `FeeAccountingDb` into `backend/src/db.ts`: extended the `Db` interface, spread `createFeeAccountingDb(sql)` into `createDb`, exported types + the helper. The factory consumes the same `sql` argument so transactional `createDb(_, txSql)` calls compose without code changes.\n52\t\n53\t**Verification**:\n54\t- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (one pre-existing warning in `contracts/api-envelope.ts`, unchanged).\n55\t- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n56\t- Skipped vitest: no call sites yet ŌĆö the dedicated unit test file lands in the next checklist item.\n57\t\n58\t**Notes**:\n59\t- `getFeeAuditSnapshot` is implemented now rather than stubbed ŌĆö the SQL is small and deferring it would force the next `[review]` iteration to re-revisit shape decisions. The dedicated audit-snapshot section can refine if needed.\n60\t- All large lamport sums are returned as strings (matching `getPendingBalanceByUserId`), with `BigInt` arithmetic in the snapshot composition to avoid Number precision loss across many high-value allocations.\n61\t- Insert helpers return the row whether newly-inserted or pre-existing, so retry-driven settlement code can rely on the return type.\n62\t\n63\t## Iteration 2 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:43:31Z ŌĆö OK\n64\t- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n65\t\n66\t---\n67\t\n68\t## Iteration 3 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n69\t\n70\t**Item**: Add `backend/src/__tests__/fee-accounting.test.ts` covering `calculateFeeAllocation` and the `fee_allocation_events` CHECK constraint.\n71\t\n72\t**Outcome**: Success.\n73\t\n74\t**Changes**:\n75\t- Added `backend/src/__tests__/fee-accounting.test.ts` with 12 tests:\n76\t  - Pure unit coverage for `calculateFeeAllocation`: 0% bps, 10000 bps, mid-range bps, dust always lands in profit (single-lamport + 7-lamport mid-bps cases), `feeLamports = 0` across the bps grid, max-bps absorbs the entire fee, components-sum-to-fee invariant on a 9 ├Ś 10 grid of (fee, bps) pairs, and input-validation throws (negative/non-integer fee, negative/over-10000/non-integer bps).\n77\t  - DB-backed coverage: a hand-crafted `INSERT` whose components don't sum to `fee_lamports` is rejected with the exact constraint name `ck_fee_allocation_components_sum`, and a parallel valid insert succeeds and is cleaned up.\n78\t- Added `src/__tests__/fee-accounting.test.ts` to `vitest.integration.files.ts` (test holds a Postgres handle, so it belongs in the integration job).\n79\t\n80\t**Verification**:\n81\t- `pnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/fee-accounting.test.ts` ŌĆö 12/12 passed.\n82\t- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (only pre-existing `contracts/api-envelope.ts` warning, unchanged).\n83\t- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n84\t\n85\t**Notes**:\n86\t- Migration `026_fee_accounting_audit.sql` had not been applied to the local dev DB; ran it through `psql` and inserted a `_migrations` row so the test can rely on the table being present. Production runs migrations on startup, so no follow-up needed.\n87\t- The DB constraint test uses random `source_id` + `wallet` strings to stay isolated from any concurrent fixture data and explicitly cleans up its own row.\n88\t\n89\t## Iteration 3 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:48:00Z ŌĆö OK\n90\t- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n91\t\n92\t## Iteration 3 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:50:06Z ŌĆö OK\n93\t- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n94\t\n95\t---\n96\t\n97\t## Iteration 4 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n98\t\n99\t**Item**: `[review]` retrospective for the Foundations section (migration + helpers + unit tests).\n100\t\n101\t**Outcome**: No change after review.\n102\t\n103\t**What I looked at**:\n104\t- `backend/migrations/026_fee_accounting_audit.sql` ŌĆö three tables, CHECK constraints + partial indexes already in place; `wallet`/`updated_at` adds on `fee_bucket_debits` are cheap and forensically useful.\n105\t- `backend/src/db/fee-accounting.ts` ŌĆö `calculateFeeAllocation` is integer-safe with input validation; the `RESERVED_OR_SPENT_STATUSES` constant maps 1:1 to the FR-3 acceptance language; insert helpers are idempotent on the spec-mandated unique keys; snapshot uses BigInt composition to avoid Number precision loss across many high-value rows.\n106\t- `backend/src/__tests__/fee-accounting.test.ts` ŌĆö covers helper edge cases (0 fee, dust, max bps, validation throws) plus a DB CHECK round-trip with the exact constraint name.\n107\t\n108\t**Considered, rejected**:\n109\t- Tightening `insertFeeBucketDebit.amountLamports` from `number | string` to `number` only ŌĆö permissive form doesn't hurt callers; no force-multiplier benefit.\n110\t- Wrapping `getFeeAuditSnapshot` in a `REPEATABLE READ` transaction ŌĆö snapshot is forensic, not a hot path; the natural inter-query race is acceptable for accounting evidence.\n111\t- Merging `active` + `completed` accumulators in the snapshot ŌĆö keeping them separate preserves forensic visibility into how much capacity is reserved vs. permanently spent.\n112\t\n113\t**Verification**:\n114\t- Spec-only edit (one checkbox flip + history append). No code changed.\n115\t\n116\t## Iteration 4 ŌĆö 2026-05-01 ŌĆö review (no diff)\n117\t\n118\t## Iteration 4 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:52:13Z ŌĆö OK\n119\t- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n120\t\n121\t---\n122\t\n123\t## Iteration 5 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n124\t\n125\t**Item**: Extend `recordReferralEarnings` in `backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` so FlipYou's `settleMatch` writes one `fee_allocation_events` row per unique player (referred and non-referred).\n126\t\n127\t**Outcome**: Success.\n128\t\n129\t**Changes**:\n130\t- `backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`:\n131\t  - Imported `calculateFeeAllocation` from `../db/fee-accounting.js`.\n132\t  - Restructured `recordReferralEarnings` to no longer short-circuit when the player has no profile or no referral link. Every unique player now produces a `fee_allocation_events` row via `db.insertFeeAllocation`. Non-referred players get `referrer_user_id = null`, `referral_rate_bps = 0`, `referral_lamports = 0`. The legacy `referral_earnings` insert still happens only when a referrer exists.\n133\t  - The split is computed once via `calculateFeeAllocation(feeLamports, referrerRateBps)`, and `referrerEarnedLamports` is now sourced from the helper instead of a duplicate `Math.floor` so the two ledgers cannot drift.\n134\t  - Updated docstring + log strings to reflect the broader purpose (\"fee accounting row\" vs. \"referral earning\"); preserved the existing duplicate-key idempotent-skip branch.\n135\t  - Function still runs inside the caller's `txDb` so allocation writes share atomicity with the rest of settlement.\n136\t\n137\t**Notes**:\n138\t- The function is shared between FlipYou (`settleMatch`) and Pot Shot (`settleLordRound`). Extending it in place naturally satisfies the next checklist item too ŌĆö the dedupe map already produces one row per `(round, wallet)` for Pot Shot. The Pot Shot iteration will confirm the wiring and check off.\n139\t- Close Call settles via a different path (`worker/settlement.ts` / `closecall-clock.ts`), so it remains unwired and is the third settlement-producer item.\n140\t- Allocation rows are go-forward only ŌĆö no backfill of pre-migration rounds (per FR-1).\n141\t\n142\t**Verification**:\n143\t- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (only the pre-existing `contracts/api-envelope.ts` warning, unchanged).\n144\t- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n145\t- Skipped vitest: integration test for the new write path lands in the dedicated test item further down the section.\n146\t\n147\t## Iteration 5 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:56:29Z ŌĆö OK\n148\t- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n149\t\n150\t---\n151\t\n152\t## Iteration 6 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n153\t\n154\t**Item**: Apply the allocation write inside `settleLordRound` (Pot Shot) in `backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`, summing multiple entries per wallet into one allocation row per (round, wallet).\n155\t\n156\t**Outcome**: Success ŌĆö confirmation iteration. The wiring already lands correctly because of how iteration 5 was structured.\n157\t\n158\t**What was verified**:\n159\t- `recordReferralEarnings` is shared between FlipYou and Pot Shot. Iteration 5 made it write `fee_allocation_events` for every unique player (referred or not). The dedupe map at `settle-tx.ts:144-148` sums multiple entries per wallet into a single `wagerLamports` total before any DB work runs.\n160\t- `settleLordRound` already calls the same hook inside its `db.withTransaction` block (`settle-tx.ts:741-751`) with `serializedEntries.map((e) => ({ wallet: e.player, wagerLamports: e.amountLamports }))`. The hook then collapses repeated wallets to one row keyed by the spec-mandated `(source_type, source_id, wallet)` UNIQUE.\n161\t- Idempotency: a Pot Shot retry hits the UNIQUE-conflict path inside `insertFeeAllocation` (ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING + re-select) and is logged as an idempotent skip ŌĆö same shape as FlipYou.\n162\t- Per-player attribution: per-wallet `feeLamports = floor(walletWagerSum * feeBps / 10_000)`. The sum across wallets approximates (within at most NŌłÆ1 lamports of floor-rounding dust) the on-chain `floor(totalAmountLamports * feeBps / 10_000)`. This per-player basis is the right accounting unit per FR-1; the on-chain treasury figure remains the source of truth for treasury inflow.\n163\t\n164\t**Changes**:\n165\t- No code changes. Spec checkbox flipped + history entry appended.\n166\t\n167\t**Verification**:\n168\t- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (only the pre-existing `contracts/api-envelope.ts` warning, unchanged).\n169\t- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n170\t- Skipped vitest: integration coverage for the Pot Shot allocation write lands in the dedicated `[test]` checklist item later in the section.\n171\t\n172\t**Notes**:\n173\t- Close Call still settles via a different path (`worker/settlement.ts` / `closecall-clock.ts`). It remains unwired and is the next checklist item.\n174\t\n175\t## Iteration 6 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:59:19Z ŌĆö OK\n176\t- **Log**: iteration-006.log\n177\t\n178\t---\n179\t\n180\t## Iteration 7 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n181\t\n182\t**Item**: Add allocation write to the Close Call settlement path so the third game wires into `fee_allocation_events`.\n183\t\n184\t**Outcome**: Success.\n185\t\n186\t**Changes**:\n187\t- `backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`: exported the existing `recordReferralEarnings` helper. No logic change ŌĆö same dedupe map, same per-player allocation write, same idempotent error handling. The helper has always been the right tool here; only a one-keyword visibility change was required.\n188\t- `backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`:\n189\t  - Imported `recordReferralEarnings` from `./settle-tx.js`.\n190\t  - Added `referralDefaultRateBps: number` to `CloseCallClockDeps` so the helper can resolve KOL rates with the same default as FlipYou/Pot Shot.\n191\t  - Inside `settleRound`'s existing `db.withTransaction` block, after `txDb.insertTransactions(txParams)` and before `upsertGameEntries`, called `recordReferralEarnings(txDb, ŌĆ”)` with `gameType: \"closecall\"`, `roundId` (= `String(Number(minuteTs))`), the resolved `feeBps` from `PlatformConfig`, and `players` mapped from `allEntries`. The hook only runs on non-refund settlements (refunds take no on-chain fee ŌåÆ no allocation to record). The transaction guarantees allocation writes share atomicity with the rest of Close Call settlement.\n192\t- `backend/src/index.ts`: passed `referralDefaultRateBps: config.referralDefaultRateBps` to `createCloseCallClockWorker`.\n193\t- `backend/src/__tests__/integration-settlement.test.ts`: passed `referralDefaultRateBps: 1000` to the in-test worker (matches the FlipYou/Pot Shot fixtures already in this file).\n194\t\n195\t**Notes**:\n196\t- Used `sourceType: \"closecall\"` (via `gameType` reuse) rather than the spec's loose hint `'closecall_round'` to stay aligned with the existing FlipYou/Pot Shot rows (`flipyou`, `potshot`). Source-type strings only tag provenance ŌĆö the spec accepts the iteration's call here, and consistency across the three games matters more than a per-game suffix.\n197\t- Per-wallet attribution: each wallet's `feeLamports = floor(walletWagerSum ├Ś feeBps / 10_000)` (helper-internal). Across many wallets this can drift up to a few lamports from the on-chain `floor(totalPool ├Ś feeBps / 10_000)` because the on-chain fee is computed on the aggregate pool, not per wallet. This is the same accounting-vs-treasury split the Pot Shot iteration accepted: per-player allocation is the audit unit; treasury inflow stays anchored on chain.\n198\t- Refunds (zero or one entrant on either side, equal close, or zero entries total): on-chain takes 0 fee, so no allocation rows. The `if (!isRefund && allEntries.length > 0)` guard makes this explicit.\n199\t- Allocation rows are go-forward only ŌĆö no backfill of pre-migration rounds (per FR-1).\n200\t\n201\t**Verification**:\n202\t- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (only the pre-existing `contracts/api-envelope.ts` warning, unchanged).\n203\t- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n204\t- Skipped vitest: integration coverage for the Close Call allocation write lands in the dedicated `[test]` checklist item later in the section, alongside FlipYou + Pot Shot integration assertions.\n205\t\n206\t## Iteration 7 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T20:03:59Z ŌĆö OK\n207\t- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n208\t\n209\t---\n210\t\n211\t## Iteration 8 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n212\t\n213\t**Item**: Add settlement integration coverage asserting that after FlipYou + Pot Shot + Close Call settlement, `fee_allocation_events` contains the expected rows for both referred and non-referred players, components sum to `fee_lamports`, and a duplicate settle attempt is a no-op.\n214\t\n215\t**Outcome**: Success.\n216\t\n217\t**Changes**:\n218\t- Added `backend/src/__tests__/integration-fee-allocation.test.ts` with three tests:\n219\t  1. **FlipYou full lifecycle** ŌĆö creates a match via the route, runs the settlement worker (full settle path through `settleMatch`), then asserts two `fee_allocation_events` rows: a non-referred creator (referrer null, rate 0, referral 0) and a referred opponent (referrer + rate set, referral split via the default 1000 bps). Components sum to `fee_lamports` for both rows. A direct replay of `recordReferralEarnings` for the same `(round, wallet)` does not duplicate rows (UNIQUE + ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING).\n220\t  2. **Pot Shot dedupe** ŌĆö calls the shared `recordReferralEarnings` helper directly with `gameType: \"potshot\"` and three entries (two from one wallet, one from another). Asserts two allocation rows, the multi-entry wallet's `wager_lamports` is the summed total, and components sum to `fee_lamports`. Replay is a no-op. Helper-direct because Pot Shot lacks the on-chain test infrastructure (decoders, program-id, mock account shapes) FlipYou and Close Call have; iteration 6 already established that the production path goes through this exact helper.\n221\t  3. **Close Call clock tick** ŌĆö sets up a closed round on the mock connection plus a Hermes price closing higher than open, runs `clock.tick()`, asserts two `fee_allocation_events` rows (referred green + non-referred red). Components sum to `fee_lamports`.\n222\t- `backend/src/__tests__/integration-test-helpers.ts`: added `fee_allocation_events`, `fee_bucket_debits`, and `fee_audit_checkpoints` to `RESET_TABLES` so subsequent test runs start clean.\n223\t- `backend/vitest.integration.files.ts`: registered the new test file so the integration job picks it up.\n224\t\n225\t**Verification**:\n226\t- `pnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/integration-fee-allocation.test.ts` ŌĆö 3/3 passed (Ōēł9s).\n227\t- `pnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/integration-settlement.test.ts` ŌĆö 8/8 still passing (regression check on the helpers change).\n228\t- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (only the pre-existing `contracts/api-envelope.ts` warning, unchanged).\n229\t- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n230\t\n231\t**Notes**:\n232\t- Source-type strings asserted in the test (`flipyou`, `potshot`, `closecall`) match what iterations 5ŌĆō7 already wired up via the shared helper.\n233\t- The replay assertions rely on the helper's logger producing an \"idempotent skip\" for the conflicting wallet, which is the production retry path under settlement worker exponential backoff.\n234\t\n235\t## Iteration 8 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T20:11:30Z ŌĆö OK\n236\t- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n237\t\n238\t## Iteration 8 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T20:12:05Z ŌĆö OK\n239\t- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n240\t\n241\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7a59072f-9629-42fa-9b0e-370a41c8b6fc","uuid":"750ac196-07c1-405f-95f6-3db320cbf1eb","timestamp":"2026-05-01T20:12:33.646Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/306-fee-accounting-audit/history.md","content":"# Implementation History ŌĆö 306-fee-accounting-audit\n\nIteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\nattempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\nof every iteration to understand prior context.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 1 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n\n**Item**: Create `backend/migrations/026_fee_accounting_audit.sql`.\n\n**Outcome**: Success.\n\n**Changes**:\n- Added `backend/migrations/026_fee_accounting_audit.sql` with three tables:\n  - `fee_allocation_events` ŌĆö allocation ledger. UNIQUE on `(source_type, source_id, wallet)`, CHECK that the three component lamport columns sum to `fee_lamports`, CHECK `referral_rate_bps BETWEEN 0 AND 10000`, plus a non-negative-amount guard. Indexed on `created_at`, with partial indexes on `referrer_user_id` and `user_id` (the audit snapshot's per-user/per-referrer queries).\n  - `fee_bucket_debits` ŌĆö bucket debit ledger. UNIQUE on `(bucket, debit_type, source_id)`, CHECK `bucket IN ('referral','promotions','profit')`, CHECK status enum matches the spec. Indexed on `(bucket, status)` and `(created_at)`. Partial index on `(user_id, bucket, status)` for `getUserReferralAvailable`.\n  - `fee_audit_checkpoints` ŌĆö bounded acceleration snapshots. Stores period bounds, row counts, bucket totals, ending balances, hashes. UNIQUE on `period_end`, plus a `period_end > period_start` guard.\n\n**Verification**:\n- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (one pre-existing warning in `contracts/api-envelope.ts`, unchanged).\n- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n- Skipped vitest: this iteration is SQL only, no TS code changed.\n\n**Notes**:\n- Added a `wallet` column to `fee_bucket_debits` to allow per-user queries to be human-debuggable; not strictly required by the spec but cheap.\n- Added an `updated_at` column on debits ŌĆö needed for the lockstep claim/debit status sync in a later iteration.\n- No data migration: ledger is go-forward only per FR-1 last bullet.\n\n## Iteration 1 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:36:11Z ŌĆö OK\n- **Log**: iteration-001.log\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 2 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n\n**Item**: Create `backend/src/db/fee-accounting.ts` with `calculateFeeAllocation` helper and typed DB methods. Wire onto the `Db` interface.\n\n**Outcome**: Success.\n\n**Changes**:\n- Added `backend/src/db/fee-accounting.ts`:\n  - `calculateFeeAllocation(feeLamports, referrerRateBps)` ŌĆö pure FR-2 split (referral floor ŌåÆ promotions floor on remainder ├Ś 20% ŌåÆ profit absorbs dust). Validates non-negative integer fee + bps in `[0, 10000]`.\n  - `insertFeeAllocation` ŌĆö writes one allocation row, idempotent on `(source_type, source_id, wallet)` via `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` + re-select.\n  - `insertFeeBucketDebit` ŌĆö writes one debit row, idempotent on `(bucket, debit_type, source_id)`.\n  - `updateFeeBucketDebitStatus(bucket, debitType, sourceId, status)` ŌĆö transitions debit status, bumps `updated_at`. Returns `undefined` if the row is missing.\n  - `getReferralBucketAvailable()` ŌĆö global referral bucket: sum of allocation referral_lamports minus sum of `pending|processing|error|completed` referral debits.\n  - `getUserReferralAvailable(userId)` ŌĆö per-user referrer balance, same shape.\n  - `getFeeAuditSnapshot()` ŌĆö totals + per-bucket allocated/active/completed/pendingClaimReserves/failed/available, plus `invariantViolations` (rows where components ŌēĀ fee) and `overdrawnBuckets`. Treats `pending|processing|error|completed` as reserved/spent, excludes `failed`. `auditFrom` is `MIN(created_at)`.\n- Wired `FeeAccountingDb` into `backend/src/db.ts`: extended the `Db` interface, spread `createFeeAccountingDb(sql)` into `createDb`, exported types + the helper. The factory consumes the same `sql` argument so transactional `createDb(_, txSql)` calls compose without code changes.\n\n**Verification**:\n- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (one pre-existing warning in `contracts/api-envelope.ts`, unchanged).\n- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n- Skipped vitest: no call sites yet ŌĆö the dedicated unit test file lands in the next checklist item.\n\n**Notes**:\n- `getFeeAuditSnapshot` is implemented now rather than stubbed ŌĆö the SQL is small and deferring it would force the next `[review]` iteration to re-revisit shape decisions. The dedicated audit-snapshot section can refine if needed.\n- All large lamport sums are returned as strings (matching `getPendingBalanceByUserId`), with `BigInt` arithmetic in the snapshot composition to avoid Number precision loss across many high-value allocations.\n- Insert helpers return the row whether newly-inserted or pre-existing, so retry-driven settlement code can rely on the return type.\n\n## Iteration 2 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:43:31Z ŌĆö OK\n- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 3 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n\n**Item**: Add `backend/src/__tests__/fee-accounting.test.ts` covering `calculateFeeAllocation` and the `fee_allocation_events` CHECK constraint.\n\n**Outcome**: Success.\n\n**Changes**:\n- Added `backend/src/__tests__/fee-accounting.test.ts` with 12 tests:\n  - Pure unit coverage for `calculateFeeAllocation`: 0% bps, 10000 bps, mid-range bps, dust always lands in profit (single-lamport + 7-lamport mid-bps cases), `feeLamports = 0` across the bps grid, max-bps absorbs the entire fee, components-sum-to-fee invariant on a 9 ├Ś 10 grid of (fee, bps) pairs, and input-validation throws (negative/non-integer fee, negative/over-10000/non-integer bps).\n  - DB-backed coverage: a hand-crafted `INSERT` whose components don't sum to `fee_lamports` is rejected with the exact constraint name `ck_fee_allocation_components_sum`, and a parallel valid insert succeeds and is cleaned up.\n- Added `src/__tests__/fee-accounting.test.ts` to `vitest.integration.files.ts` (test holds a Postgres handle, so it belongs in the integration job).\n\n**Verification**:\n- `pnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/fee-accounting.test.ts` ŌĆö 12/12 passed.\n- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (only pre-existing `contracts/api-envelope.ts` warning, unchanged).\n- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n\n**Notes**:\n- Migration `026_fee_accounting_audit.sql` had not been applied to the local dev DB; ran it through `psql` and inserted a `_migrations` row so the test can rely on the table being present. Production runs migrations on startup, so no follow-up needed.\n- The DB constraint test uses random `source_id` + `wallet` strings to stay isolated from any concurrent fixture data and explicitly cleans up its own row.\n\n## Iteration 3 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:48:00Z ŌĆö OK\n- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n\n## Iteration 3 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:50:06Z ŌĆö OK\n- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 4 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n\n**Item**: `[review]` retrospective for the Foundations section (migration + helpers + unit tests).\n\n**Outcome**: No change after review.\n\n**What I looked at**:\n- `backend/migrations/026_fee_accounting_audit.sql` ŌĆö three tables, CHECK constraints + partial indexes already in place; `wallet`/`updated_at` adds on `fee_bucket_debits` are cheap and forensically useful.\n- `backend/src/db/fee-accounting.ts` ŌĆö `calculateFeeAllocation` is integer-safe with input validation; the `RESERVED_OR_SPENT_STATUSES` constant maps 1:1 to the FR-3 acceptance language; insert helpers are idempotent on the spec-mandated unique keys; snapshot uses BigInt composition to avoid Number precision loss across many high-value rows.\n- `backend/src/__tests__/fee-accounting.test.ts` ŌĆö covers helper edge cases (0 fee, dust, max bps, validation throws) plus a DB CHECK round-trip with the exact constraint name.\n\n**Considered, rejected**:\n- Tightening `insertFeeBucketDebit.amountLamports` from `number | string` to `number` only ŌĆö permissive form doesn't hurt callers; no force-multiplier benefit.\n- Wrapping `getFeeAuditSnapshot` in a `REPEATABLE READ` transaction ŌĆö snapshot is forensic, not a hot path; the natural inter-query race is acceptable for accounting evidence.\n- Merging `active` + `completed` accumulators in the snapshot ŌĆö keeping them separate preserves forensic visibility into how much capacity is reserved vs. permanently spent.\n\n**Verification**:\n- Spec-only edit (one checkbox flip + history append). No code changed.\n\n## Iteration 4 ŌĆö 2026-05-01 ŌĆö review (no diff)\n\n## Iteration 4 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:52:13Z ŌĆö OK\n- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 5 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n\n**Item**: Extend `recordReferralEarnings` in `backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` so FlipYou's `settleMatch` writes one `fee_allocation_events` row per unique player (referred and non-referred).\n\n**Outcome**: Success.\n\n**Changes**:\n- `backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`:\n  - Imported `calculateFeeAllocation` from `../db/fee-accounting.js`.\n  - Restructured `recordReferralEarnings` to no longer short-circuit when the player has no profile or no referral link. Every unique player now produces a `fee_allocation_events` row via `db.insertFeeAllocation`. Non-referred players get `referrer_user_id = null`, `referral_rate_bps = 0`, `referral_lamports = 0`. The legacy `referral_earnings` insert still happens only when a referrer exists.\n  - The split is computed once via `calculateFeeAllocation(feeLamports, referrerRateBps)`, and `referrerEarnedLamports` is now sourced from the helper instead of a duplicate `Math.floor` so the two ledgers cannot drift.\n  - Updated docstring + log strings to reflect the broader purpose (\"fee accounting row\" vs. \"referral earning\"); preserved the existing duplicate-key idempotent-skip branch.\n  - Function still runs inside the caller's `txDb` so allocation writes share atomicity with the rest of settlement.\n\n**Notes**:\n- The function is shared between FlipYou (`settleMatch`) and Pot Shot (`settleLordRound`). Extending it in place naturally satisfies the next checklist item too ŌĆö the dedupe map already produces one row per `(round, wallet)` for Pot Shot. The Pot Shot iteration will confirm the wiring and check off.\n- Close Call settles via a different path (`worker/settlement.ts` / `closecall-clock.ts`), so it remains unwired and is the third settlement-producer item.\n- Allocation rows are go-forward only ŌĆö no backfill of pre-migration rounds (per FR-1).\n\n**Verification**:\n- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (only the pre-existing `contracts/api-envelope.ts` warning, unchanged).\n- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n- Skipped vitest: integration test for the new write path lands in the dedicated test item further down the section.\n\n## Iteration 5 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:56:29Z ŌĆö OK\n- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 6 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n\n**Item**: Apply the allocation write inside `settleLordRound` (Pot Shot) in `backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`, summing multiple entries per wallet into one allocation row per (round, wallet).\n\n**Outcome**: Success ŌĆö confirmation iteration. The wiring already lands correctly because of how iteration 5 was structured.\n\n**What was verified**:\n- `recordReferralEarnings` is shared between FlipYou and Pot Shot. Iteration 5 made it write `fee_allocation_events` for every unique player (referred or not). The dedupe map at `settle-tx.ts:144-148` sums multiple entries per wallet into a single `wagerLamports` total before any DB work runs.\n- `settleLordRound` already calls the same hook inside its `db.withTransaction` block (`settle-tx.ts:741-751`) with `serializedEntries.map((e) => ({ wallet: e.player, wagerLamports: e.amountLamports }))`. The hook then collapses repeated wallets to one row keyed by the spec-mandated `(source_type, source_id, wallet)` UNIQUE.\n- Idempotency: a Pot Shot retry hits the UNIQUE-conflict path inside `insertFeeAllocation` (ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING + re-select) and is logged as an idempotent skip ŌĆö same shape as FlipYou.\n- Per-player attribution: per-wallet `feeLamports = floor(walletWagerSum * feeBps / 10_000)`. The sum across wallets approximates (within at most NŌłÆ1 lamports of floor-rounding dust) the on-chain `floor(totalAmountLamports * feeBps / 10_000)`. This per-player basis is the right accounting unit per FR-1; the on-chain treasury figure remains the source of truth for treasury inflow.\n\n**Changes**:\n- No code changes. Spec checkbox flipped + history entry appended.\n\n**Verification**:\n- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (only the pre-existing `contracts/api-envelope.ts` warning, unchanged).\n- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n- Skipped vitest: integration coverage for the Pot Shot allocation write lands in the dedicated `[test]` checklist item later in the section.\n\n**Notes**:\n- Close Call still settles via a different path (`worker/settlement.ts` / `closecall-clock.ts`). It remains unwired and is the next checklist item.\n\n## Iteration 6 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T19:59:19Z ŌĆö OK\n- **Log**: iteration-006.log\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 7 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n\n**Item**: Add allocation write to the Close Call settlement path so the third game wires into `fee_allocation_events`.\n\n**Outcome**: Success.\n\n**Changes**:\n- `backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts`: exported the existing `recordReferralEarnings` helper. No logic change ŌĆö same dedupe map, same per-player allocation write, same idempotent error handling. The helper has always been the right tool here; only a one-keyword visibility change was required.\n- `backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`:\n  - Imported `recordReferralEarnings` from `./settle-tx.js`.\n  - Added `referralDefaultRateBps: number` to `CloseCallClockDeps` so the helper can resolve KOL rates with the same default as FlipYou/Pot Shot.\n  - Inside `settleRound`'s existing `db.withTransaction` block, after `txDb.insertTransactions(txParams)` and before `upsertGameEntries`, called `recordReferralEarnings(txDb, ŌĆ”)` with `gameType: \"closecall\"`, `roundId` (= `String(Number(minuteTs))`), the resolved `feeBps` from `PlatformConfig`, and `players` mapped from `allEntries`. The hook only runs on non-refund settlements (refunds take no on-chain fee ŌåÆ no allocation to record). The transaction guarantees allocation writes share atomicity with the rest of Close Call settlement.\n- `backend/src/index.ts`: passed `referralDefaultRateBps: config.referralDefaultRateBps` to `createCloseCallClockWorker`.\n- `backend/src/__tests__/integration-settlement.test.ts`: passed `referralDefaultRateBps: 1000` to the in-test worker (matches the FlipYou/Pot Shot fixtures already in this file).\n\n**Notes**:\n- Used `sourceType: \"closecall\"` (via `gameType` reuse) rather than the spec's loose hint `'closecall_round'` to stay aligned with the existing FlipYou/Pot Shot rows (`flipyou`, `potshot`). Source-type strings only tag provenance ŌĆö the spec accepts the iteration's call here, and consistency across the three games matters more than a per-game suffix.\n- Per-wallet attribution: each wallet's `feeLamports = floor(walletWagerSum ├Ś feeBps / 10_000)` (helper-internal). Across many wallets this can drift up to a few lamports from the on-chain `floor(totalPool ├Ś feeBps / 10_000)` because the on-chain fee is computed on the aggregate pool, not per wallet. This is the same accounting-vs-treasury split the Pot Shot iteration accepted: per-player allocation is the audit unit; treasury inflow stays anchored on chain.\n- Refunds (zero or one entrant on either side, equal close, or zero entries total): on-chain takes 0 fee, so no allocation rows. The `if (!isRefund && allEntries.length > 0)` guard makes this explicit.\n- Allocation rows are go-forward only ŌĆö no backfill of pre-migration rounds (per FR-1).\n\n**Verification**:\n- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (only the pre-existing `contracts/api-envelope.ts` warning, unchanged).\n- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n- Skipped vitest: integration coverage for the Close Call allocation write lands in the dedicated `[test]` checklist item later in the section, alongside FlipYou + Pot Shot integration assertions.\n\n## Iteration 7 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T20:03:59Z ŌĆö OK\n- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 8 ŌĆö 2026-05-01\n\n**Item**: Add settlement integration coverage asserting that after FlipYou + Pot Shot + Close Call settlement, `fee_allocation_events` contains the expected rows for both referred and non-referred players, components sum to `fee_lamports`, and a duplicate settle attempt is a no-op.\n\n**Outcome**: Success.\n\n**Changes**:\n- Added `backend/src/__tests__/integration-fee-allocation.test.ts` with three tests:\n  1. **FlipYou full lifecycle** ŌĆö creates a match via the route, runs the settlement worker (full settle path through `settleMatch`), then asserts two `fee_allocation_events` rows: a non-referred creator (referrer null, rate 0, referral 0) and a referred opponent (referrer + rate set, referral split via the default 1000 bps). Components sum to `fee_lamports` for both rows. A direct replay of `recordReferralEarnings` for the same `(round, wallet)` does not duplicate rows (UNIQUE + ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING).\n  2. **Pot Shot dedupe** ŌĆö calls the shared `recordReferralEarnings` helper directly with `gameType: \"potshot\"` and three entries (two from one wallet, one from another). Asserts two allocation rows, the multi-entry wallet's `wager_lamports` is the summed total, and components sum to `fee_lamports`. Replay is a no-op. Helper-direct because Pot Shot lacks the on-chain test infrastructure (decoders, program-id, mock account shapes) FlipYou and Close Call have; iteration 6 already established that the production path goes through this exact helper.\n  3. **Close Call clock tick** ŌĆö sets up a closed round on the mock connection plus a Hermes price closing higher than open, runs `clock.tick()`, asserts two `fee_allocation_events` rows (referred green + non-referred red). Components sum to `fee_lamports`.\n- `backend/src/__tests__/integration-test-helpers.ts`: added `fee_allocation_events`, `fee_bucket_debits`, and `fee_audit_checkpoints` to `RESET_TABLES` so subsequent test runs start clean.\n- `backend/vitest.integration.files.ts`: registered the new test file so the integration job picks it up.\n\n**Verification**:\n- `pnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/integration-fee-allocation.test.ts` ŌĆö 3/3 passed (Ōēł9s).\n- `pnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/integration-settlement.test.ts` ŌĆö 8/8 still passing (regression check on the helpers change).\n- `cd backend && pnpm lint` ŌĆö exit 0 (only the pre-existing `contracts/api-envelope.ts` warning, unchanged).\n- `cd backend && pnpm typecheck` ŌĆö exit 0.\n\n**Notes**:\n- Source-type strings asserted in the test (`flipyou`, `potshot`, `closecall`) match what iterations 5ŌĆō7 already wired up via the shared helper.\n- The replay assertions rely on the helper's logger producing an \"idempotent skip\" for the conflicting wallet, which is the production retry path under settlement worker exponential backoff.\n\n## Iteration 8 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T20:11:30Z ŌĆö OK\n- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n\n## Iteration 8 ŌĆö 2026-05-01T20:12:05Z ŌĆö OK\n- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n\n","numLines":241,"startLine":1,"totalLines":241}}}
